â€œMainâ€ to enable â€œF12 bootâ€.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>F12</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Open live USB and go to â€œGpartedâ€.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Move as per requirements. Here is a <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/114503/how-to-resize-your-ubuntu-partitions/">nice tutorial</a> from
â€œhow-to-geekâ€</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>If unallocated part is not next to the part you want to expand,
this then involves moving all the partitions so that the
unallocated is next. This has the â€œWarning-dangerâ€ message even for
â€œmovingâ€ a partition. Do AT YOUR OWN RISK.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<h2 id="caveats">Caveats</h2>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>â€œUnallocatedâ€ needs to be close to the partition you are interested
in.</p>
